http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/bangalore/Jayachandra-upset-over-delay-in-setting-up-special-courts-to-try-land-grab-cases/article13994413.ece

Expressing regret over the delay by the Revenue Department in setting up special courts to try land-grab cases even after passing an order four months ago, Minister for Law and Parliamentary Affairs T.B. Jayachandra on Monday cautioned that further delay would lead to confrontation with activists opposing land encroachment in the State. Addressing presspersons, Mr. Jayachandra told the department to pull up its socks as the committee, led by freedom fighter H.S. Doreswamy, on encroachment and land-grab of government land, had threatened to launch a protest against the failure of the government in setting up special courts.One spl court in BengaluruHowever, one special court would be set up soon in Bengaluru and the Revenue Department had almost finalised the building, the Minister said.The special court will be headed by a retired high court judge and will have two judicial and two revenue members. The judicial member will be a district judge and revenue member an official of Principal Secretary rank.State-wide jurisdictionThe courts being set up under the Karnataka Land Grabbing Prohibition Act would have State-wide jurisdiction.